cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SE 

This paper is primarily focused on cybersecurity and the development of a system to monitor and understand cyberattacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, specifically temporal word embeddings, to analyze and model the data, which suggests that it could also fit into the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the system for improving situational awareness and developing proactive defenses, which could place it in the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
